# logi-dd-gui (Slint GUI) is only present in this build when the building
# host's rustc met Slint's MSRV (>= 1.92); see debian/rules. Its runtime
# stack (windowing/input/GL) is therefore a Recommends, not a hard Depends,
# so the package still installs cleanly on hosts where the GUI was omitted.
# Derived from `ldd`/`strings` on the built binary (Slint dlopen's the
# wayland/X11/GL bits rather than linking them, so ldd alone misses them).
Recommends: libwayland-client0, libwayland-egl1, libxkbcommon0,
 libxkbcommon-x11-0, libx11-6, libx11-xcb1, libxcb1, libxcursor1, libxi6,
 libxrender1, libegl1, libgl1, libfontconfig1, libfreetype6
Description: DKMS kernel driver for Logitech TrueForce direct-drive wheels
 Force feedback, TrueForce texture routing, and G HUB-equivalent settings
 exposed through sysfs for the Logitech RS50 and G PRO direct-drive racing
 wheels. The module is built and installed for the running kernel by DKMS,
 and rebuilt automatically on kernel upgrades.
 .
 The module is named hid-logitech-dd and is scoped to the direct-drive
 wheel USB IDs (c276 RS50 native, c272 G PRO Xbox/PC and RS50 compat, c268
 G PRO PS/PC). It coexists with the in-tree hid-logitech-hidpp driver,
 which continues to serve every other Logitech device, so no blacklist is
 needed.
 .
 Also installs userspace companions built from the repo's Rust workspace:
 logi-ffb, a DirectInput force-feedback proxy, logi-dd, a terminal
 settings UI, logi-tf-sim, a simulated-TrueForce daemon driven by game
 telemetry, and logi-dd-gui, a graphical settings app (GPL-3.0-or-later;
 see debian/copyright, with a desktop menu entry), built when the
 toolchain's rustc supports it.
 .
 TrueForce in Proton sims additionally needs Logitech's proprietary signed
 SDK DLLs, which are not shipped by this package; see the bundled Getting
 Started guide.
